claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A flowchart outlining influenza vaccine dosing recommendations for children aged 6 months through 8 years based on prior vaccination history, indicating whether one or two doses of the 2022–23 influenza vaccine are needed. The figure relates to vaccine dosing schedules and does not address antigenic match or Flublok’s alignment with WHO- or FDA-selected strains, so it does not support the claim. Note: Image clearly shows dosing recommendations and lacks any reference to Flublok or antigenic match.
